The pscf_fd program is designed for problems in which fields depend on 
only a single variable, and uses a a regular one-dimensional mesh to 
discretize the solutions.  This program uses a simple file format for
w and c fields that contains a header and data section. 

The header provides values for the number of number of grid points, 
denoted by nx, and the number of monomer types, denoted by nm.

Each row in the data section starts with the index associated with a 
grid point, followed by values of all fields at that grid point. Each
column after the first gives the values of the field associated with 
a specific monomer type, listed in order of increasing monomer type
index.

<h3> Example: </h3>
