<h3> Boundary conditions: </h3>

The pscf_fd program solves the underlying modified diffusion equation
using a boundary condition that requires the 1D spatial derivative of 
the propagator to vanish at both endpoints. 

An additional constraint is applied when a problem is solved in 
canonical ensemble, in which values of volume fraction phi (rather 
than chemical potential mu) are specified for all polymer and 
solvent species. In this case, by convention, the value of the
chemical potential is taken to zero for the last monomer type 
at the last grid point. This convention is why a value of 0.0000 
is visible for the last column of the last row in the above example.

